Head yellow with vertex, a longitudinal median line following mid-cranial suture and antennal insertions black. Labrum yellow to brownish. Surface flat, mid-cranial suture generally apparent, deep but sometimes blurred, almost obliterated. Punctures moderately impressed, scattered, denser along the inner ocular rim. Punctures on vertex smaller and shallower. Setosity reduced to few scattered setae on vertex, close to inner eye rims, lower part of clypeus and labrum. Antennae (
Fig. 13m
) normally shaped with antennomeres 1–5 brownish and the remainders black.
